<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<root>
    <doclet-version-NOT-library-version>1.00</doclet-version-NOT-library-version>
    <class>
        <name>B4R::B4RTM1637Display</name>
        <shortname>TM1637Display</shortname>
        <comment>B4R Library rTM1637Ex
 20210525 rwbl</comment>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="Initialize">Initialize</name>
            <comment>Initializes the object.
PinClk - Pin connected to the Clock pin.
PinDIO - Pin connected to the Data Input/output pin pin.</comment>
            <returntype>B4R::void</returntype>
            <parameter>
                <name>PinClk</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>PinDIO</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
        </method>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="SetBrightness">SetBrightness</name>
            <comment>Sets the brightness of the display.
The setting takes effect when a command is given to change the data being displayed.
brightness - Number from 0 (lowes brightness) to 7 (highest brightness)
on - Turn the display on or off</comment>
            <returntype>B4R::void</returntype>
            <parameter>
                <name>brightness</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>on</name>
                <type>bool</type>
            </parameter>
        </method>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="SetSegments">SetSegments</name>
            <comment>Displays arbitrary data.
Each byte represents a single digit.
Each bit represents a segment.
Position - Position from which to start the modification (0 - leftmost, 3 - rightmost).
The 7 LED segments:
A
F B
G
E C
D
 DP
DP is the dot (8th LED) if supported by the display.</comment>
            <returntype>B4R::void</returntype>
            <parameter>
                <name>Segments</name>
                <type>Byte[]</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>Position</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
        </method>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="ShowNumberDec">ShowNumberDec</name>
            <comment>Displays the decimal number.</comment>
            <returntype>B4R::void</returntype>
            <parameter>
                <name>Number</name>
                <type>Int</type>
            </parameter>
        </method>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="ShowNumberDec2">ShowNumberDec2</name>
            <comment>Displays the decimal number.
Number - Number to be shown.
LeadingZero - Whether to add leading zeroes.
Length - Number of digits to set.
Position - Position of the least significant digit (0 - leftmost, 3 - rightmost).</comment>
            <returntype>B4R::void</returntype>
            <parameter>
                <name>Number</name>
                <type>Int</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>LeadingZero</name>
                <type>bool</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>Length</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>Position</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
        </method>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="ShowNumberDec3">ShowNumberDec3</name>
            <comment>Similar to ShowNumberDec2. Controls the decimal dots or colon based on the DotsMask. Pass 0xFF to enable all dots / colons.
The argument is a bitmask, with each bit corresponding to a dot
between the digits (or colon mark, as implemented by each module). The MSB is the
leftmost dot of the digit being update. For example, if Position is 1, the MSB of DotsMask
will correspond the dot near digit no. 2 from the left. Dots are updated only on
those digits actually being update (that is, no more than Length digits)</comment>
            <returntype>B4R::void</returntype>
            <parameter>
                <name>Number</name>
                <type>Int</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>LeadingZero</name>
                <type>bool</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>Length</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>Position</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>DotsMask</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
        </method>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="Clear">Clear</name>
            <comment>Clear the display (uses SetSegments with 0 data)</comment>
            <returntype>B4R::void</returntype>
        </method>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="GetChar">GetChar</name>
            <comment>Get Char from the font char table.
Index - AscII character index 0 - 127)
Font - 1=AscII, 2=Siekoo</comment>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
            <parameter>
                <name>Index</name>
                <type>Int</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>Font</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
        </method>
        <method>
            <name DesignerName="ShowText">ShowText</name>
            <comment>Display a text with max 4 characters in ascii range 0-127. Not all characters are supported.
Position - Starting position of the text: 0=leftmost .. 3=rightmost
Font - 1=AscII, 2=Siekoo
Examples:
Display text HaLo startig at pos 0 (leftmost): tmDisplay.ShowText("HaLo",0)
Display text 9C starting at position 1: tmDisplay.ShowText("9C",1)</comment>
            <returntype>B4R::void</returntype>
            <parameter>
                <name>Text</name>
                <type>B4R::B4RString*</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>Position</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
            <parameter>
                <name>Font</name>
                <type>Byte</type>
            </parameter>
        </method>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="SEG_A">B4RTM1637Display_SEG_A</name>
            <comment>Define the 7 segments for function SetSegments</comment>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="SEG_B">B4RTM1637Display_SEG_B</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="SEG_C">B4RTM1637Display_SEG_C</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="SEG_D">B4RTM1637Display_SEG_D</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="SEG_E">B4RTM1637Display_SEG_E</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="SEG_F">B4RTM1637Display_SEG_F</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="SEG_G">B4RTM1637Display_SEG_G</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="FONT_ASCII">B4RTM1637Display_FONT_ASCII</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="FONT_SIEKOO">B4RTM1637Display_FONT_SIEKOO</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
        <field>
            <name DefineMethod="true" DesignerName="SPECIAL_DEGREE">B4RTM1637Display_SPECIAL_DEGREE</name>
            <returntype>Byte</returntype>
        </field>
    </class>
